    "department": "Internships",
    "description": "ABOUT POLYMARKET\n\nPolymarket is the world's largest prediction market platform. We enable individuals to express views on real-world events by trading on outcomes across politics, economics, sports, culture, and current affairs. Built as a peer-to-peer marketplace with no centralized \"house,\" Polymarket aggregates diverse opinions into transparent, market-based probabilities that reflect collective expectations about the future.\n\nWe're growing fast: both in volume ($21B traded in 2025) and in adoption as an alternative news source. Our ambition is to become a ubiquitous beacon of truth in global media, powered by fast, reliable, and deeply technical market infrastructure.\n\n\n\n\n\nWE'RE BUILDING OUR 2026 INTERNSHIP PROGRAM\n\nWe're laying the groundwork for our Summer 2026 internship program and want to hear from exceptional students and early-career candidates who are excited about what we're building.\n\nWe're interested in talent across a wide range of functions, including:\n\n - Engineering – backend, frontend, smart contracts, data infrastructure\n\n - Product – product management\n\n - Design – product and brand design\n\n - Data – data science and analytics\n\n - Markets – trading, market operations, and research\n\n - Marketing – growth, content, and brand\n\n - Business Development – partnerships and growth\n\n - Strategic Finance – FP\u0026A, strategy, and analytics\n\n - Operations – business and program operations\n\n - Legal – regulatory, compliance, and policy\n\nIf you're passionate about prediction markets and the future of information, we want to meet you.\n\n\n\n\n\nHOW TO APPLY\n\nThis is a general interest posting. Once the Summer 2026 internship program formally launches, we’ll email everyone who has submitted their information with a link to apply. In the meantime, you can submit your resume and area(s) of interest using the form below so we can keep you in mind as the program takes shape. We look forward to hearing from you!",
